cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the recent advances in Reinforcement Learning (RL) and proposes a user simulator based on Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) to pre-train and evaluate new recommendation algorithms. It also touches upon other sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it deals with recommender systems, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it uses RL-based techniques, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it involves user behavior modeling, and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as it aims to improve user experiences.
